ðŸ“¢ Discord Webhook Message Sender

ðŸ“œ Description

This Python script allows you to send an automatic message to a Discord channel via a Webhook. You can use this script to send notifications, announcements, or any type of automated messages to your server.

ðŸš€ How to Use

1. Create a Discord Webhook

Go to your Discord server settings.

Select a channel (or create a new one) where you want the message to be sent.

In the channel settings, click on "Integrations" and then "Webhooks".

Create a new webhook and copy the URL.



2. Install Python and Requests

Ensure you have Python installed on your system. You can download Python here.

Install the requests library by running the following command:

pip install requests



3. Set up the Script

Download or copy the discord_webhook.py script into a folder.

Open the script in a text editor and replace the webhook_url with the webhook URL you copied from Discord.

Modify the message in the script to customize what will be sent.



4. Run the Script

Open a terminal and navigate to the folder where the script is located.

Run the script by executing the following command:

python discord_webhook.py



5. Message Sent

After running the script, the message will be sent to the specified Discord channel.
